programme.title: From Ashes to Arrow: Wyoming Archery Antelope Hunting After Heat, Wildfire & Flood
programme.desc:
In this unforgettable episode of Pursue the Wild, I take you deep into a Wyoming antelope season that tested more than just skill or patience—it tested everything. From blistering 100-degree days spent in the blind, to a wildfire that scorched my ranch, and a flash flood that followed just days later, Mother Nature threw it all at me.
But through the chaos, I stayed the course—checking trail cams, caring for my mules, and trusting the process. When the rut ramped up and a beautiful buck finally stepped into bow range—on my own land—it was more than just a hunt. It was a moment of redemption, resilience, and deep gratitude.
This is a story about perseverance, faith, and the wild magic that only Wyoming can deliver.

With her dad having drawn an early rifle antelope tag, plans shift from alpine timber to wide-open desert. From bugling bulls to sharp-eyed pronghorn, this episode is all about tradition, family, and adapting to whatever the wild has in store.

programme.title: Home Range: Strong Women, Wild Hunts
programme.desc:
Kristy Titus opens the gates to her Wyoming home range to welcome three women from Girls with Guns Clothing for a week of learning, laughter, and rifle training. Together, they dive into the fundamentals—mounting optics, zeroing rifles, and trajectory validating at distance, all while building confidence and camaraderie in the field.
But the lessons don't stop at the range. With new skills in hand and hearts full of determination, the team sets out on a whitetail deer hunt rooted in mentorship, shared goals, and the spirit of the wild.
This episode is a celebration of strong women, self-reliance, and the power of passing it on.
Special thanks to Brant & Ellen Hillman - Rangeland Hunting Adventures

Join Kristy Titus as she rolls out from Wyoming and heads straight into the heart of the Midwest for one of her favorite traditions- whitetail hunting in Missouri.
After tuning up her archery skills at Total Archery Challenge, she hits the road- ready for those crisp rut-filled mornings, big bucks, and all the unforgettable moments that come with time spent in the stand. There's something special about the whitetail rut—and the miles, memories, and magic that come with it.
In this episode of Pursue the Wild, Kristy takes you along for the ride. It's a journey packed with adrenaline, gratitude, and all the reasons we keep coming back to the woods!
